! [[Audio Video Interleave|AVI]]
| [[Microsoft]]
| {{dunno}}
| {{Yes}}<ref name="ACM VBR">[[Audio Compression Manager|ACM]] cannot handle VBR audio streams in AVI files. Thus, software using [[Audio Compression Manager|ACM]] to read audio from AVI files will not be able to handle VBR audio streams correctly, even though such files are compliant to the AVI file specification. This is a limitation of the [[Audio Compression Manager|ACM]], not of the AVI file format.</ref>
| {{Yes}}<ref name="AVI VFR">Although AVI is not designed for variable framerates, it is possible to use them without creating a non-standard file by using 0-byte chunks for skipped frames. However it requires framerate to be set to [[Least common multiple]] of all framerates used, and produces slight overhead compared to true VFR.</ref>
| {{partial|Yes, via third party modifications}}
| {{partial|Yes, via third party modifications}}
| {{yes2|Almost anything through [[Video for Windows|VFW]]}}
| {{yes2|Almost anything through [[Audio Compression Manager|ACM]]; [[Vorbis]] is problematic }}<ref name="Vorbis in AVI">Although [[FFmpeg]] has introduced a solution to put Vorbis audio into AVI files, this "extension" is not compatible with existing Vorbis decoders for [[DirectShow]] and [[Audio Compression Manager|ACM]]. Putting Vorbis in an AVI container is very problematic. The way [[Nandub]] stored Vorbis audio streams in AVI files occasionally caused desychronisation when seeking.</ref>
| {{yes}} through [[Resource Interchange File Format|RIFF]] chunks
