{{Infobox Software | name = GrandView | logo = | screenshot = File:GrandView_2.0_splash_screen_1990.png | caption = GrandView 2.0 splash screen | developer = [[Symantec]] | latest_release_version = 2.0 | latest_release_date = 1990 | operating_system = [[MS-DOS]] | genre = [[Personal information management]] [[Outliner]] | license = Proprietary | website = }}
'''GrandView''' is <!-- USE IS AS COPIES STILL EXIST --> an [[outliner|outlining]] and [[personal information management]] (PIM) application originally developed by [[Living Videotext]].<ref name= "PC Mag">{{cite journal |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=Eq0wALnyM_MC&pg=PA34&lpg=PA34&dq=%22grandview%22+%22friend%22+outliner&source=bl&ots=Mu4Qvw94r1&sig=QNN7btHAgcANCcARHNi-gcNHf04&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JVVjVKbkA9eyyATHnoHYDg&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=%22grandview%22%20%22friend%22%20outliner&f=false |title= GrandView Outliner Integrates Classic Features and New Tools |work= [[PC Magazine]] |date= June 14, 1988 |accessdate= February 13, 2015}}</ref> Living Videotext was acquired by [[Symantec]] in 1987. Grandview was sold until the early 1990s and is no longer supported by Symantec. It closely resembled PC-Outline, an outliner for IBM PCs of the 1980s. Grandview was derived from the same software.
==Reception== ''[[BYTE]]'' in 1989 listed GrandView as among the "Distinction" winners of the BYTE Awards, stating that it was "packed with goodies" and worth the time necessary to learn how to use it.<ref name="byte198901">{{Cite magazine |date=January 1989 |title=The BYTE Awards |url=https://archive.org/stream/byte-magazine-1989-01/1989_01_BYTE_14-01_PC_Communications_and_Annual_Awards_and_Digitizing_Tablets#page/n378/mode/2up |magazine=BYTE |page=332}}</ref>
